# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# │       │             │
# │       │             └─► Summary in present tense (lowercase, no period)
# │       │
# │       └─► Scope: user-service|catalog-service|loan-service|
# │                    notification-service|gateway|frontend|
# │                    shared|infra|deps|docs|repo|auth|api|ui|admin|tests
# │
# └─► Type: feat|fix|docs|style|refactor|perf|test|build|ci|chore|revert
#
# Allowed types:
#   feat     ✨ A new feature
#   fix      🐛 A bug fix
#   docs     📝 Documentation only changes
#   style    💄 Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
#   refactor ♻️  A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     ⚡️ A code change that improves performance
#   test     ✅ Adding missing or correcting existing tests
#   build    📦 Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#   ci       👷 Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   chore    🔧 Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#   revert   ⏪️ Reverts a previous commit
#
# Examples:
#   feat(auth): add JWT refresh token endpoint
#   fix(loan-service): resolve overdue detection race condition
#   docs(frontend): update component API reference
#   refactor(catalog-service): extract ISBN validation to domain
#   test(shared): add unit tests for Result type
#   ci(infra): add commitlint workflow
#
# Body (optional):
#
# Explain the motivation for the change, what problem it solves,
# and any trade-offs made. Wrap at 72 characters.
#
# Footer (optional):
#   Closes #123, #456
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>
#
